00:41:51,630 --> 00:41:54,820
When you have no family left.

459
00:41:54,820 --> 00:41:57,720
I can't believe that you came here for money.

460
00:41:59,170 --> 00:42:01,750
Can you promise me one thing?

461
00:42:01,750 --> 00:42:05,270
That you will keep our conversation private?

462
00:42:07,260 --> 00:42:09,280
I promise.

463
00:42:11,020 --> 00:42:14,290
I came here because there is something I must do.

464
00:42:16,390 --> 00:42:18,500
What is it?

465
00:42:23,130 --> 00:42:25,680
Can you help me?

466
00:42:25,680 --> 00:42:27,440
How could I?

467
00:42:30,130 --> 00:42:34,250
Don't lose me. That's all you have to do.

468
00:42:48,500 --> 00:42:51,460
Is this suicide?

469
00:42:51,460 --> 00:42:53,620
Or a trap?

470
00:42:54,790 --> 00:42:57,610
Miss Eugene, why did you come to Korea?

471
00:42:58,620 --> 00:43:02,840
Because I made a mistake and I was forced to leave. At my boss's recommendation.

472
00:43:02,840 --> 00:43:05,040
Good excuse.

473
00:43:06,220 --> 00:43:08,690
Why do you think it's an excuse?

474
00:43:09,770 --> 00:43:13,670
Didn't you honestly want to find your roots?

475
00:43:13,670 --> 00:43:16,420
Who I am now is what defines me.

476
00:43:16,420 --> 00:43:19,150
Why would I need the past?

477
00:43:26,600 --> 00:43:32,260
Why is it me of all people?  There are many other good detectives.

